        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Repair invoke-style plain-text tool calls",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Extend plain-text tool-call repair to recognize XML-ish invoke calls with named parameter arguments.\n- Keep streamed invoke-style tool-call text buffered so it can be promoted into structured tool-call events instead of leaking as assistant text.\n- Allow standalone text tool-call promotion when the terminal reason is `toolUse`, improving compatibility with models such as Opus 4.8 that may emit XML-ish tool-call text.\n- Preserve the existing `length` fallback promotion behavior for complete under-cap plain-text tool calls.\n\n## Behavior\nThis only affects malformed/plain-text tool-call repair paths. Normal structured tool calls continue to use the existing provider-native flow unchanged.\n\n## Real behavior proof (required for external PRs)\n\n- Behavior or issue addressed: Opus 4.8-style XML-ish plain-text tool-call output can be repaired into a structured tool-call event instead of being emitted as assistant text. The existing `length` fallback path is still promoted.\n- Real environment tested: Redacted local OpenClaw checkout running this PR branch with the OpenClaw provider stream compatibility wrapper through Node/tsx.\n- Exact steps or command run after this patch: Ran a local OpenClaw wrapper smoke command that feeds two real wrapper inputs: an existing bracketed plain-text tool call ending with `length`, and an XML-ish invoke plain-text tool call ending with `toolUse`.\n- Evidence after fix (screenshot, recording, terminal capture, console output, redacted runtime log, linked artifact, or copied live output):\n\n```text\nlength fallback: event types = [\"toolcall_start\", \"toolcall_delta\", \"done\"]\nlength fallback: done.reason = \"toolUse\"\nlength fallback: tool name = \"exec\"\nlength fallback: arguments = { \"command\": \"date\" }\n\ninvoke toolUse: event types = [\"toolcall_start\", \"toolcall_delta\", \"done\"]\ninvoke toolUse: done.reason = \"toolUse\"\ninvoke toolUse: tool name = \"exec\"\ninvoke toolUse: arguments = { \"command\": \"date\" }\n```\n\n- Observed result after fix: Both compatibility paths produced structured `toolCall` content and the wrapper emitted `toolcall_start`, `toolcall_delta`, and final `done` events. The existing `length` fallback still promotes instead of passing through as assistant text.\n- What was not tested: No live external model request is included in this proof; provider credentials and endpoints are intentionally omitted. Normal structured tool calls are unchanged by this path and were not re-proven here.\n- Proof limitations or environment constraints: Runtime output is redacted and uses a local OpenClaw wrapper smoke run so no private endpoint, account, gateway, session, host, IP address, or token is exposed.\n- Before evidence (optional but encouraged): Current main lacks support for invoke-style XML-ish openings with named parameter tags in the plain-text tool-call parser, so the same shape can leak as assistant text instead of being promoted.\n\n## Tests and validation\n- `git diff --check upstream/main`\n- `corepack pnpm exec oxfmt --check packages/tool-call-repair/src/grammar.ts packages/tool-call-repair/src/payload.ts packages/tool-call-repair/src/promote.ts packages/tool-call-repair/src/stream-normalizer.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run/attempt.tool-call-normalization.ts src/plugin-sdk/provider-stream-shared.test.ts src/shared/text/tool-call-shaped-text.test.ts src/shared/text/tool-call-shaped-text.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.unit-fast.config.ts src/shared/text/tool-call-shaped-text.test.ts --reporter=dot --maxWorkers=1`\n- Local OpenClaw wrapper smoke run covering preserved `length` fallback promotion and invoke-style `toolUse` promotion.\r\n",
        "branch": "fix/plain-text-invoke-tool-calls",
